<TITLE> Muhith heads recession taskforce </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Abdur Rahim Harmachi bdnews24.com senior correspondent Dhaka, Mar 17 (bdnews24.com)  The government formed Tuesday the much talked-about 27-strong taskforce with finance minister AMA Muhith as its head to face off the global recession fallout, he said. Agriculture minister Motia Chowdhury, commerce minister Faruq Khan, textiles minister Abdul Latif Siddiqi and labour and manpower minister Khandaker Mosharraf Hossain will sit on the taskforce, Muhith told bdnews24.com by phone Tuesday evening. Its members will include one representative from each of the major parties, including the main opposition BNP, economists, specialists and businessmen, he said. The finance minister said letters had been sent to BNP and Jatiya Party asking them to name their representatives. The relevant department of the finance ministry has been instructed to issue a circular on the constitution of the taskforce. The circular was expected Tuesday, he said. The taskforce will advise the government on strategies to protect the country from the crisis, Muhith said. The decision was taken at a cabinet meeting, the minister said, speaking after a seminar Monday on "Global Financial Crisis and Impact on Bangladesh". bd
